v3:
INPUT: NewCase, threshold
DATA: CrimeCases + Victims

Normalize input (location, gender, method)

STEP 1: Group filtering (reduce search space)
    SELECT cases FROM AllCases
    WHERE case.location == input.location
       OR case.method == input.method

STEP 2: For each caseA in filtered cases:
    FOR each caseB in filtered cases AFTER caseA:

        score = 0

        IF caseA.location == caseB.location:
            score++

        IF caseA.method == caseB.method:
            score++

        IF caseA.victim.gender == caseB.victim.gender:
            score++

        IF age ranges overlap:
            score++

        IF score >= threshold:
            store (caseA.id, caseB.id, score)

RETURN results + performance metrics


v4:
INPUT:
    NewCase (Location, Method, VictimGender, AgeMin, AgeMax)
    threshold
    K (Top-K)

DATA: CrimeCases + Victims

Normalize input

STEP 1: Filter candidates (indexed selection)
    candidates = SELECT cases FROM database
                 WHERE case.location == input.location
                    OR case.method == input.method
                    OR case.victim.gender == input.gender

STEP 2: Initialize empty TopK list

STEP 3: FOR each case IN candidates:

            score = 0

            IF case.location == input.location:
                score++

            IF case.method == input.method:
                score++

            IF case.victim.gender == input.gender:
                score++

            IF age ranges overlap:
                score++

            IF score >= threshold:
                insert (case.id, score) into TopK list

                sort TopK descending
                keep only top K elements

STEP 4: RETURN TopK results + metrics
